Amazing, amazing food! So comforting and delicious. The Pho Chay was so so yummy! Can't wait to eat here again <3

This place rocks. My family planned a 90th birthday party here for my father as a surprise and to quote him, it was “the best day of my life”. The restaurant sat down with us, helped plan the menu for 25 people, including a few special …

We went on trip in the US for 1 months, and this is our favorite restaurant! Taste good! the place is clean and modern. We can't find anything like that in France. Thanks, can't wait to come back again !!!
If you’re looking for good pho do not come here. The broth tasted like cheap cinnamon and ginger tea and the meat was sparse.

Trying to get a hold of them with my online order but their phone number is not working goes straight to message saying the voicemail is not set up. I liked them but never will I order again this is ridiculous... gonna drive there and check where my order is. UNSATISFIED.
Great service, great food, very decent portions and very clean.
Love the food and the decor here. The pho filet dac biet is authentic and aromatic. You must try it! Makes me think of home. I’m definitely coming back here for another big bowl of goodness!

The food was delicious but the place is clearly understaffed for how busy they are.  Our apps came out quickly but the pho is taking a ridiculous amount of time to follow.  I feel bad watching these two young women try to keep up with seating people, taking orders, bussing tables, serving food and handling the takeout orders.

We arrived at this place for dinner. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was a winning. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we had a great feeling. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Highly recommended.
This spot is great! Convenient prices, considerable dishes and the employees are constantly very nice.
Yum! Their garlic noodles and BBQ beef/pork are my ultimate comfort food!
Love the food.

Last week was our first time we went to this place. But It is obviously not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the excellent service, with the exceptional  dishes and fine drinks and with the decent payment. We will absolutely come back soon.
Ok location for tasty Vietnamese food. it has a great interior.
Great place to eat at!
Just okay.
Awesome place and beautiful space.
AAA+

This place was so good and the company was better! My mom Lynda, Deb, Ming and myself! They really loved Ming!
Delicious pho ga.  The best broth anywhere.  Restaurant is very clean and pleasant, service is good, and food is delicious.

We stumbled upon Lotus-and-light on our visit to LA. We were driving back from Santa Monica to Anaheim and visited this restaurant for dinner. This was unarguably the best pho we ever had. I have had Pho at many different places in Seattle. …
The food was fresh. The drinks were amazing. The young woman who  made our drinks and served us was absolutely great. The whole experience was awesome
Great food, great atmosphere, and great staff! It can get a bit crowded during the mid day lunch rush, but the food is definitely worth waiting slightly longer.
We dropped in after a Warner Bros. Studio tour, and had the most Amazing Pho we ever tasted. Thank you.

A great lunch spot for Vietnamese food. It's clean and modern looking. One of the nicer restaurants in this plaza. The beignets are the underrated hit here. If you have enough room for dessert, definitely order it.
Let me tell you, you won't regret it!! Delish!
Delicious food. The egg rolls are a must.
Really interesting and crispy egg rolls with pork mushroom filling. Pho broth is very light and mild and almost a butter flavor in it. Overall pretty good soup!
Tasty and healthy eats a bit eclectic.  Clean and helpful staff.

Food is fresh and flavorful. A little pricier than other similiar vietnamese resturant. It must be because it's near toluca lake and the nearby studios. Very consistent with there food. Love how spicy the Filet mignon and chilli rice dish …

This place is so Zen. My sister in laws and I went here for lunch on a Saturday. The vibe was super chill, the interior was spacious, bright and clean. Their food is delicious, I had the veggie rolls and chicken pho.
They had a very bad attitude and were taking wayy too long. Service is also bad and i dont think the food was very good. There was 3 people eating there and 2 of them were the workers.
Delicious and nice atmosphere
Good vietnamese restaurant. The Pho broth is okay but the filet mignon is incredibly tender and the Fried Tofu is highly recommended.

Great place, excellent service, thank you for the fabolous service young lady! Very good foods and priced reasonably. The best deep fried tofu I have ever had (on appetizer menu).  Keep up the good work!
fresh and tasty

The portions are pretty small relative to other Vietnamese restaurants out there, but the quality of the food is much better. Though a little pricy, the service and atmosphere are really nice. You get what you pay for...

I visited on a Friday night. The service was prompt and cheerful but the food could have been served faster. The beef pho was flavourful and comforting, the pork sausage rolls were well made as well. Iced Vietnamese coffee i ordered …
Amazing lunch
First experience was great. Second was a complete and utter disappointment. Horrible service.
Wonderful Thai/Vietnamese food. Bangkok Spring Rolls, Chicken over Rice, Honey Lavendar Ice Cream, all yummy. Lovely decor and welcoming staff.

I liked my meal. If you’re looking for a quick option Lotus and Light is great, they’re friendly and the restaurant is clean and comfortable. Portions are huge. The tofu was a little bland, and the noodle salad I ordered didn’t pack the punch I expected.
Fair prices, great food, service was wonderful, beer selection is fantastic, has one of my favorite beers "Red Rice Ale", and really chill atmosphere. Will come back again.

Not knowing what to expect, I was pleasantly surprised by this restaurant. The egg rolls are crispy and delicious. The Bankok rolls are also great. They come with a cilantro/basil sauce that was very delicious. I had the filet mignon with …
Food is ok if you want more authentic vietnamese food and cheaper... this will not be the place. Place is nice and clean!  But otherwise,  overall food is ok.
Amazing service and really great food. The fried tofu appetizer is a must. It is so light and the sauce complements it perfectly. Truly had an amazing experience

Amazing! I am very picky with my pho and this broth is very tasty, you don’t have to add anything to it. But my favorite dishes here that are different from other places are charbroiled pork or beef bun -vermicelli and the filet mignon basil chili if you like spicy!!!
Lovely restaurant.  Delicious food.  Great service.

Reasonable price and good pho. Their egg rolls are the best for me, the fried ones. I'm not a soft spring roll guy.
Excellent place, a little bit louder atmosphere but the food is so good I couldn't hear anything over the taste.
Egg rolls are great.
Really really nice. Lovely space. So clean. Not to mention great food.
Friendly staff, great food, everything is made from scratch. I like the pho, the bun is my favorite, and the chi goi pork is good too
Fast, clean,  great customer service! Food delicious!

Outstanding! The rice vermicelli dish with the grilled pork and egg rolls is truly amazing. The restaurant interior has a very light and open feel - clean and simple. A perfect environment for sampling the delicate flavors of Vietnamese cuisine.
Never seen Pho shop looks this good (on top of great food)
very good food..everything on the menu is well prepared.
I love this place for their vermicelli.  Nice place, casual but a nice clean creative aesthetic, and reasonable in price, too.

If you love Golden Deli in San Gabriel you'll love this place more. It's great that I finally don't have to drive all the way to the SGV to get my fix of authentic pho.  What makes this particular pho place stand out from the billion of …
Amazing Vietnamese modern food! Very clean and the food was delicious!  Highly recommend this place
Delicious!!!

Great New find; you can see and taste the quality. A simple menu with complex flavors & food that will keep you coming back! Although our server was great everyone came and checked on us. The bartender was mixing Valentine's Day concoctions …
Great food. Awesome service. One of a kind place for the Burbank area.
All appetizers were so good. I didn’t like pho as much as other dishes because it was too much grease floating to the top of the soup. Bangkok rolls was my favorite. Drinks are fantastic.
Food exceptionally well prepared. Imaginative menu. Try the Butterfly Pea iced tea, and don’t miss the fried tofu. Service excellent. Look forward to second visit.

Really great new Vietnamese restaurant in Burbank. The staff are all friendly and attentive, and the food is amazing. From the cloud like pillows of fried tofu, to the Pho and great beer and wine selection, this is a definite must try!

They were very busy the night we came in, but the servers were both so sweet and kind the whole time. The food was fantastic and they gave us a giftcard for a future visit due to longer wait times. Would highly recommend the pho and spring rolls!

I would recommend this place to anybody who likes Vietnamese food (Thai inspired). We tried the fried tofu, it was super light and super savory (fave). Also recommended would be the Bangkok noodle rolls the pho fillet and the Lotus papaya …
